\
OPERATING MODES\
\
Standalone Operating Mode			-		one and only one instance\
										caches are non-distributed and local\
										configuration file - /standalone/configuration/standalone.xml (NON OPENSHIFT)\
\
Standalone Clustered Mode			-		an instance of RH SSO on each machine you want to run a server instance\
										specific infrastructure settings networking, databases, caches, and disvocery\
										requires a shared database, load balancer in front of the cluster, \
										configuration file - /standalone/configuration/standalone-ha.xml (NON OPENSHIFT)\
\
Domain Clustered Mode				-		centrally manage and publish configuration\
										configuraiton file - /standalone/configuration/domain.xml\
\
\
\
CONFIGURATION\
\
Configuration file:\
OpenShift							-		/opt/eap/standalone/configuration/standalone-openshift.xml\
Server on Linux						-		pick one from the operating modes above\
\
\
\
Keycloak Subsystem\
the \'91server/profile/subsystem keycloak\'92 is the section that needs to be configured\
\
\
Ways of changing the. configuration:\
edit the configuration file by hand\
use the ../bin/jboss-cli.sh utility to change the configuration\
\
\
\
DATABASE\
\
Concept of RHSSO connecting with a database:\
\
Top Layer			-	HIbernate JPA - maps Java Objects to relational data\
Bottom Layer 		-	JDBC API.   -------   JDBC Driver -------- RDBMS				(This is the one that requires configuration, if at all)\
\
NOTE: JDBC Driver is a module from a JAR at the modules location\
\
\
\
MODULES\
\
To make a module work with RH-SSO:	(This might actually be a JBOSS EAP thing)\
\
Copy a jar and module.xml file into the proper location\
OpenShift path		-	/opt/eap/modules/system/layers/openshift/	followed by a directory structure in the format of the java package name - then .jar file and module.xml file\
Server on Linux		-	../modules							followed by a directory structure in the format of the java package name - then .jar file and module.xml file\
\
Configure the configuration file\
For example for postgresql jdbc driver update the subsystem/datasources and add driver in drivers\
\
