OIDC TOKEN\
\
Identity Token			-		part of OpenID Connect specification\
							identity information like username, address, email and other profile data, maybe permission data, \
\
Access Token			-		part of OpenID Connect and OAuth 2.0 specification\
							digitally signed by the realm, contains access information (like user role mappings) \
							a token that can be provided as part of an HTTP request that grants access to the service being invoked\
